# Web Service (SvelteKit)

SvelteKit frontend with TailwindCSS and Preline UI.

## Code Style
- TypeScript strict mode
- Svelte 5 runes: `$state()`, `$derived()`, `$effect()`, `$props()`
- Use ESLint and Prettier
- Type-safe API client (generated from OpenAPI)

## Svelte 5
- Use runes for reactivity
- Avoid `let` for reactive state

## TypeScript
- Explicit types
- Avoid `any` (use `unknown` if needed)
- Use interfaces for props

## Styling
- TailwindCSS utility classes
- Preline UI components
- Scoped component styles

## API Integration
- Use generated API client
- Handle errors with i18n
- Show loading states
- Validate inputs

## i18n
- All user text translatable
- Use `$_()` for translations
- Support pt-BR and en-US

## Testing
- E2E tests with Playwright
- Test error scenarios
- Test form validation

## Performance
- Code splitting
- Lazy loading routes
- Optimize images
